(http://finance.yahoo.com/charts#chart2:symbol=nyb;range=1y;compare=xlf;chartty
e=line;crosshair=on;logscale=on;source=undefined)

Insiders have been acquiring NYB stock in the $17.00 - $18.00 price range.
http://finance.yahoo.com/q/it?s=NYB

NYB's business is not leveraged to any sub-prime debt but rather to
multi-family loans which continue to perform well. The company has had no loan
losses in their niche for 28 years. Their non performing asset are low at .07%
of their total assets well below the average thrift at 0.75%. Their loan
portfolio statistics as of 9/30/07 were:
- % of total loans = 71.8%
- Average principal balance = $3.5 million
- Average loan-to-value ratio = 63.4%
- Expected weighted average life = 3.5 years

The company pays a quarterly dividend of $0.25.share and has done so for 16
consecutive quarters.

I have owned the stock for over five years and have built a position that ranks
as one of my top five. $23 is my long term target with an average cost of about
$17.

I think you have to be careful with all banks in this environment. I am
currently not buying any banks at this time but am watching WM, WFC, C, and
