That's one thing I really dislike about listed stocks. Level II doesn't give
you the whole story. If you want to buy x amount of stock on the Nasdaq, you
can at least see if there are enough shares available at a price you're willing
to pay. On NYSE, you could put in an order a penny over the ask and have zero
idea if there will be enough offered to get you a fill or if you're just going
to get a partial then push the price above what you want to pay.
